    "partners_need_to_know_arB3pd": {
      "type": "partners-need-to-know",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_item_XHecWw": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is a KOPILOT.ID NFC tag and how does it work?",
            "answer": "<p>KOPILOT.ID is a smart NFC tag linked to a participant's digital medical ID profile. When someone taps the tag with a smartphone, it instantly opens their profile with critical medical information and emergency contacts. In an emergency, this gives first responders, medics, or bystanders access to the information they need to make faster, more informed decisions when every second counts.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_3zpKMQ": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does KOPILOT.ID NFC tag require batteries, charging, or a subscription?",
            "answer": "<p>No. KOPILOT.ID NFC tags are completely battery-free and never need charging. There are also no ongoing subscription fees required for participants to use their profile, making it a simple and dependable solution for everyday use.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_KYRCin": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does KOPILOT.ID work without signal or cell service?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. The NFC tag itself works without signal, batteries, or charging, making it ideal for remote environments. When a tag is scanned, participants also receive a notification with the GPS location of the scan, helping friends and family know where the interaction took place.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": false
          }
        },
        "faq_item_B3bMyV": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What information can participants store on their profile?",
            "answer": "<p>Participants can choose to store medical conditions, allergies, medications, emergency contacts, blood type, and any other information they want accessible in an emergency. There is no mandatory information required, and participants have complete control over what appears on their profile. Information can be updated, hidden, or removed at any time through the KOPILOT.ID app.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        },
        "faq_item_yEzKUY": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the NFC tag waterproof?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. KOPILOT.ID NFC tags are built for harsh outdoor conditions and everyday use. They are waterproof, durable, and designed to withstand the environments commonly encountered in racing, riding, hiking, trail running, snow sports, and other outdoor activities.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        },
        "faq_item_LpC6GG": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can the tags be custom branded?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Tags can be customized with your organization's branding, colors, logos, and messaging to create a seamless extension of your event, product, or community.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        },
        "faq_item_k3LG8X": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who owns and manages participant information?",
            "answer": "<p>Participants create and manage their own KOPILOT.ID profile. Your organization does not receive or manage medical information, emergency contacts, or profile data.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        },
        "faq_item_WMztTz": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Who can access a participant's information?",
            "answer": "<p>The profile is designed to be accessible in an emergency. A first responder, bystander, or medic can tap the tag with a smartphone to access the participant's information. Participants control what appears on their profile and can update or deactivate it at any time.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        },
        "faq_item_GmBXbn": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens to the participant's profile after the event?",
            "answer": "<p>Participants keep ownership of their profile and can continue using it across future events, products, and tags. </p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        },
        "faq_item_GiJqQG": {
          "type": "faq_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there a minimum order quantity?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer solutions for organizations of all sizes. <a href=\"/pages/contact\" title=\"Contact\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">Contact us </span> </a>to discuss your specific needs and partnership goals.</p>",
            "open_by_default": true,
            "in_more": true
          }
        }
      },
